# ks_models

A custom ML library with custom model implementations.

## Installation

Install the package in editable mode for local development:

```bash
pip install -e .
```

This installs the package in "editable" mode, meaning:
- Changes to source code are immediately available
- The package is accessible from any Python environment on your system
- No need to reinstall after code changes

## Usage

```python
import ks_models
from ks_models import models

# Add your model implementations here
```

## Dependencies

- numpy >= 1.20.0
- pandas >= 1.3.0

## Project Structure

```
ks_models/
├── ks_models/              # Main package directory
│   ├── __init__.py        # Package initialization
│   └── models/            # ML models module
│       ├── __init__.py
│       └── (your model files here)
├── pyproject.toml         # Package configuration
└── README.md              # This file
```

## Development

After making changes to the source code, they will be immediately available since the package is installed in editable mode. No reinstallation needed.

